com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.filters

Class TokenPlaceholder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.joliciel.talismane.tokeniser.filters.TokenPlaceholder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<TokenPlaceholder>

    public class TokenPlaceholder
extends Object
implements Comparable<TokenPlaceholder>
    A place-holder that will be replaced by a proper token when tokenising.
    A placeholder where isSingleToken() returns false is an attribute placeholder, which only adds attributes. In this case, only a single attribute of a given key can be added per token. If two attribute placeholders overlap and assign the same key, the one with the lower start index is privileged for all tokens, and the other one is skipped for all tokens. If they have the same start index, the one with the higher end index is priveleged for all tokens, and the other one is skipped for all tokens.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli
